  <prompt>
    Author `TrustFrameInstructionInjector` (NEW) per architecture §8.3 (citation enforcement model) + P3. Produces the canonical persona instruction text that tells the LLM:
    (1) precomputed summaries on file cards are upload-time approximations marked "NOT authoritative";
    (2) for any legally-precise question (specific clauses, exact wording, dates, parties, dollar amounts), call `recall_session_file` with `requireCitations: true` and cite the source in the answer;
    (3) do not quote precomputed summaries from the file cards as if they were the source.
    The injection is a `string` (≤500 tokens) that the per-turn composer adds between persona + user content.
  </prompt>

  <role>SPAARKE platform BFF developer. Expert in persona injection + architecture P3 trust framing + legal-domain accuracy semantics.</role>

  <goal>
    `TrustFrameInstructionInjector.cs` exists with `ITrustFrameInstructionInjector` interface + `BuildAsync(ChatInvocationContext ctx, CancellationToken ct) → string`. Returns the canonical trust-frame text from architecture §8.3, optionally customized per session context (e.g., when no files uploaded, abbreviate the file-related instructions).
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      Per architecture P3 + §8.3. Load-bearing for legal-domain accuracy — the trust frame is what STOPS the LLM from quoting hallucinated precomputed summaries as "the source." Task 076 produces the cards; this task tells the LLM how to TREAT them.
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/PlaybookChatContextProvider.cs</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/SprkChatAgentFactory.cs</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Memory/MemoryCompositionService.cs</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="architecture P3">Canonical text per architecture §8.3 — quote it verbatim as the seed; allow per-context customization (e.g., when no files exist, condense).</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-013">Service lives in `Services/Ai/Memory/` (per-turn composition layer) — within AI module.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-014">Output is byte-stable across turns when session context fingerprint unchanged — supports static prefix cache hit.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-015">Tier-1 logging: sessionId, instructionLength. NEVER instruction body.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-029">Per-task publish-size measurement; small expected.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Instruction text is STATELESS code (no LLM call); deterministic output.</constraint>
  </constraints>

